Here is the Java code to store the first 10 'https url' search results from a Bing search for 'house' in a Hashmap:

```
import java.io.BufferedReader;
import java.io.InputStreamReader;
import java.net.HttpURLConnection;
import java.net.URL;
import java.util.HashMap;

public class BingSearch {

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {

        HashMap<Integer, String> results = new HashMap<>();
        String query = "house";
        String source = "https://www.bing.com/search?q=" + query;

        URL url = new URL(source);
        HttpURLConnection con = (HttpURLConnection) url.openConnection();

        BufferedReader in = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(con.getInputStream()));
        String inputLine;

        int count = 1;
        while ((inputLine = in.readLine()) != null && count <= 10) {
            if (inputLine.contains("https://")) {
                String[] strArr = inputLine.split("\"");
                for (String str : strArr) {
                    if (str.contains("https://")) {
                        results.put(count, str);
                        count++;
                        break;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        in.close();

        System.out.println("First 10 'https url' search results for the query '" + query + "' are:");
        for (int key : results.keySet()) {
            System.out.println(key + "." + results.get(key));
        }
    }
}
```

This code first creates an empty HashMap called `results`, which will store the search results. Then, it sets the search query as "house" and constructs the URL to search on Bing.

After that, it opens a connection to the URL and reads the content using a BufferedReader. It reads each line and checks if it contains "https://". If it does, it splits the line using the double quote (") delimiter, and searches for the first substring containing "https://". It puts this result string in the HashMap and increases the count variable. It does this for the first 10 results.

Finally, it prints out the first 10 'https url' search results for the query "house" using a for loop over the HashMap.

